OL,6,FThe Titanic was a luxury passenger
OL,7,Fliner which sank in the North Atlantic
OL,8,FOcean on 15 April 1912 after striking
OL,9,Fan iceberg.
OL,11,FThe deep-water investigation
OL,12,Fspecialist used two remotely operated
OL,13,Fvehicles at depths of around 3,800
OL,14,Fmetres to produce the images of the
OL,15,Fwreck which were then made into a
OL,16,Fmoving scan.
OL,18,FThe images also revealed a necklace on
OL,19,Fthe seabed that had not been seen in
OL,20,Fmore than one hundred years.
